President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in Oklahoma due to wildfires that occurred from April 11 to April 20, 2018. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Traci L. Brasher has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future if requested by the state and warranted by further damage assessments. For more information, media should contact the FEMA News Desk.